==English==
===Noun===

=== Etymology ===

from Greek word ''kryos'', "icy cold"

=== Definition ===

''Cryopreservation'' is the act of preserving biological tissue at cryogenic temperatures, typically at -80°C (dry ice temperature) or -196°C (the boiling point of liquid nitrogen).  

